33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  I feel this is very important!</span><hr size=1> Talked to some guild mates about this last night and one gave me the great idea to add it here.  As I understand it in Velious the dwarves are at war with the giants and the giants are at war with the dwarves and dragons.  Not 100 per cent sure how the dragons and dwarves feel about each other.  Anyway you sort of have to pick a side in this war/wars to do some really nice quests and by sideing with one side you become KOS to the other/others.  Problem here is with grouping, friendships, and the guild as a whole.  ie I pick to side with the giants and two other guildmates, who I am grouped with side with the dwarves and they are attacked by a wondering giant, if I do nothing but watch and cheer my friends and guildmates they will die, if I help I kill my faction with the giants (at this point I would have already destoryed my faction with the dwarves).  I think this should be talked about on a guild level and I know some people do not read the webpage like they should.  Maybe we should try and talk about this at the next guild meeting or make a meeting just for this.  I do feel this is very important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uhaldorrodlah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haldor Rodlah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/01 4:23:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I feel this is very important!</span><hr size=1> Guild Civil War?<br>
<br>
Damn Verant!<br>
<br>
Good idea Ger'mish. I'm not up to date on the dwarf war in Velious but from you explination I can see how that would be a problem. <br>
<br>
I move that the all knowing officers fix it! (J/K) hehe<br>
 <p><IMG SRC="http://www.geocities.com/haldor13021/1FACE.gif">

Haldor Rodlah "The Crazy Druid"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sentry>Sentry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/01 5:15:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I feel this is very important!</span><hr size=1> Hmm, not sure there's an answer to that.  Personally, I was planning to pick a side (not necessarily the same one) with each character and play it that way.  I guess that would require checking with people you group with (guild or not) to see if they are pro-Giant or pro-Dwarf.  Not fun, that.<br>
<br>
Sentry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uthiaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thiaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/01 6:17:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Giants vs DWarves</span><hr size=1> Dragons also hate giants, so by killing giants you raise faction with dragons, probably if you kill dwarves the same happens no sure.. I pick dwarves to side with. But hear best quests are actually in the giant town, but well.. there is some wicked drops in giant town and it will be some time until i can join on raids in Icewall keep.. I believe you should pick whatever makes you feel good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ugermish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Germish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/01 10:04:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I feel this is very important!</span><hr size=1> Doing what makes you happy is very important and its what makes EQ fun.  But I feel what I am saying is important.  When half a guild group gets eaten by giants and all the other half of the group says is &quot;sorry guys but the giants are our friends.  Guess you sided with the dwarves?  I'll try and find you a xp res.&quot;  After that it will not feal very fun anymore.  Trust will break down and people will be finding different people to group with. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ugermish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Germish</A> at: 3/4/01 10:05:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ubrambler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brambler</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/3dlgowu2.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/01 11:00:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/leaf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I feel this is very important!</span><hr size=1> As far as the class specific armor quests go, the results from the Kael (giants), Thugardin (Dorfs), and Skyshrine (Dragons) are basically identical.  Each piece has the same effect no matter where you get it and there are only small differences in the stats (one may be 5sv magic, 3sv poison and the other 3sv magic, 5sv poison).  There are some pretty good non-class specific quests in Kael and they seem to be a bit better then those available in Thugardin (although I did quest for a very nice 3ac 3int 3wis 30mana 3sv mag + cold ranged item from the dorfs), havent seen much info on the dragons quests so I'm not sure how those compare but I'm pretty sure that when I first arrived in Velious I was KOS to giants as well as Dragons and only the dorfs would have me so I chose to go with them (besides, waxin a bunch of giants and wurms seemed alot funner then toastin dorfs).  Either way, theres plenty of stuff you can hunt that wont hurt your faction with any of the groups including various animals (cougars, mammoths, snow grifs, manticores, etc), Ulthorks, Orcs, weird spider thingies in Crystal Caves and thats just what I've seen in the 3 or 4 zones I've checked out so far.  Hope this info helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC="http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/sig1.jpg"> <BR>
